Yang Haodong preached the spirit of the 6th Plenary Session of the 19th CPC Central Committee and the Provincial Party Congress in Malanshan to draw strength from the century-long history of the Party's struggle Hunan Daily, December 10 (All media reporter Gong Baiwei) According to the unified arrangement of the provincial party committee, on the morning of December 10, Yang Haodong, member of the standing committee of the provincial party committee and minister of the propaganda department of the provincial party committee, made an interactive preaching in Malanshan Video Cultural and Creative Park to deeply study and implement the spirit of the 6th Plenary Session of the 19th CPC Central Committee, study Implement the spirit of Xi Jinping, the general secretary of Hunan important speech important instructions and instructions, study and implement the spirit of the 12th Party Congress of the province. Yang Haodong explained the core meaning and practical requirements of the spirit of the Plenary Session in an in-depth, comprehensive and systematic manner from three aspects, including ideal belief and original mission, self-revolution and youthful party, party leaders and party theory, combined with his own perception and personal experience. He pointed out that the spirit of the plenary session should be combined with the spirit of the important instructions and instructions of General Secretary Xi Jinping to Hunan and the spirit of the provincial party congress, and learn them in a coherent way, enhance the ideological consciousness, political consciousness and action consciousness of defending the "two establishments" and doing the "two safeguards", and steadfastly follow the principle of the "two establishments". The study will strengthen the ideological consciousness, political consciousness and action consciousness of defending "two establishments" and doing "two safeguards", and firmly follow the direction guided by General Secretary Xi Jinping. In the interactive exchange session, grassroots cadres, enterprise representatives and youth representatives asked questions about the relationship between the three historical resolutions, how to understand the decisive significance of the "two establishments", how to grasp the orientation of cultural enterprises, how to draw strength from the 100-year history of the Party for the youth in the new era, etc. Yang Haodong answered them one by one with common language and vivid examples. He also sent a warm message to the young members that they should draw strength from the 100-year history of the Party, unite closely around the Party Central Committee, follow the Party unswervingly, and write their responsibilities and responsibilities with youthful dedication.
